'''James Kirchick''' (born ) is an   and .<ref>www.boston.com/news/globe/magazine/articles/2007/08/05/left_out/</ref>  
Kirchick grew up in the  suburbs and is a 2006 graduate of .  <ref>  www.boston.com/news/globe/magazine/articles/2007/08/05/left_out/ </ref>  <ref>[http://www.examiner.com/a-527696~James_Kirchick__Columbia_University_must_maintain_its_good_name.html James Kirchick: Columbia University must maintain its good name - Examiner.com<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>  
Kirchick began to attract national attention in January 2008, when, in an article published in ''The New Republic'', he reported on decades-worth of newsletters published by Republican congressman and presidential candidate Ron Paul, characterized by "obsession with conspiracies, sympathy for the right-wing militia movement, and deeply held bigotry against blacks, Jews, and gays."
Kirchick's political views and commentary have not fit neatly into any particular box, though his tone is often caustic and strident. Although he once canvassed for  and (in a 2006 Wall Street Journal article) identified himself as a "liberal Democrat"<ref>http://www.opinionjournal.com/diary/?id=110008051</ref>, he has also called himself a "conservative," "libertarian," and "recovering leftist."<ref>www.boston.com/news/globe/magazine/articles/2007/08/05/left_out/</ref> Kirchick's writings since 2002 have been deeply opposed to Yale's unions and ,<ref>http://www.yaledailynews.com/articles/view/15565</ref><ref>http://www.yaledailynews.com/articles/view/8018</ref> liberal feminists,<ref>http://www.yaledailynews.com/articles/view/17071?badlink=1</ref> proponents of diversity,<ref>http://www.yaledailynews.com/articles/view/12944</ref> anti-war professors,<ref>http://www.frontpagemag.com/Articles/Printable.aspx?GUID={3E053BDD-B851-4CEA-A7AA-449D34DAB5E4}</ref> "" activists (though Kirchick is openly gay),<ref>http://www.yaledailynews.com/articles/view/16580</ref> and opponents of the Iraq War.<ref>http://www.yaledailynews.com/articles/view/13169</ref><ref>http://www.yaledailynews.com/articles/view/10463</ref> His articles frequently defended Yale University and the State of Israel. <ref>[http://www.yaledailynews.com/articles/view/7843 Yale Daily News - Why I'm on the decent side of the left<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> <ref>[http://www.yaledailynews.com/articles/view/5237 Yale Daily News - Anti-Semitism at a very un-model U.N<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> Kirchick criticized campus s and gays who called American society intolerant but would not criticize the “misogynistic and homophobic regimes” of the ,”  mocking them for prioritizing " other concerns such as single-sex s and ," <ref>www.opinionjournal.com/diary/?id=110008051</ref>  <ref>[http://www.yaledailynews.com/articles/view/17071?badlink=1 Yale Daily News - Afghan politician contrasts with student<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> advocated for a return of  and military recruitment on campus, <ref>[http://www.washblade.com/2005/5-27/view/columns/recruiters.cfm Backwards ban on military recruiters - Washington Blade<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>  <ref>[http://www.yaledailynews.com/articles/view/8674 Yale Daily News - Anti-JAG policy quashes law students' free speech rights<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> asserted “the right of Israel to defend itself against annihilation,” <ref>[http://www.yaledailynews.com/articles/view/5237 Yale Daily News - Anti-Semitism at a very un-model U.N<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> criticized what he considered the "far-left atmosphere" of the campus for “applauding falsehoods” following a speech by poet Amiri Baraka hosted by the Yale African American Cultural Center, <ref>[http://www.yaledailynews.com/articles/view/7096 Yale Daily News - Applauding falsehoods at a university<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> and failing to defend liberal values of individual rights. He has also criticized what he claims are attempts by the far left to stifle public debate on campus and in the country generally.  <ref>[http://www.yaledailynews.com/articles/view/9160 Yale Daily News - Campus left silences opposing views<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> <ref>[http://www.examiner.com/a-568782~James_Kirchick__Who_is_really_stifling_honest_debate_about_the_Middle_East_.html James Kirchick: Who is really stifling honest debate about the Middle East? - Examiner.com<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>. He was among the first to refer to former member of the  and professor  as an "unrepentant terrorist" - in a piece attacking Ayer's adopted son (and classmate)<ref>http://yaledailynews.com/articles/view/17647</ref> - two years before the phrase became a catchphrase in a 2008 presidential election controversy. [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bill_Ayers_election_controversy]
